# Marketplace

This is an Angular Ionic project for a marketplace that uses npm as a package manager, Firebase for backend services, and is written in TypeScript.

## Getting Started

These instructions will get you a copy of the project up and running on your local machine for development and testing purposes.

### Prerequisites:

- Node.js and npm installed on your machine
- Angular CLI installed globally (`npm install -g @angular/cli`)
- Ionic CLI installed globally (`npm install -g @ionic/cli`)

## Installing:

Clone the repository: `git clone https://github.com/azizbenyaala98/marketplace`
Navigate into the project directory: `cd marketplace`
Install the dependencies: `npm install`

## Running the Application:

Run `ionic serve` for a dev server.
Navigate to `http://localhost:8100/`. The app will automatically reload if you change any of the source files.

## Running the Tests:

Run `ng test` to execute the unit tests via Karma.

## Building the Project:

Run ionic build to build the project. The build artifacts will be stored in the www/ directory. Use the --prod flag for a production build.

## Technologies Used

- Angular: The web framework used
- Ionic: The mobile app framework used
- npm: Dependency Management
- TypeScript: Used for static typing
- Firebase: Used for backend services

